<div type="history" n="text-constituted-from">
<head>Text Constituted From</head>
<p>Preliminary transcription (Reynolds); publications.</p>
</div>

<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>Nestor and Zenon sons of Epigonos the son of Dioscurides dedicated the fourteen columns with the capitals at their own expense to the People</p>
</div>
<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>These two columns are from a group of fourteen dedicated by by Nestor and Zenon. Another four survive from the six dedicated by Artemon (Mendel 172). For further column dedications from the Hadrianic Baths see Boulanger B<title level="m"> </title>Page 23, no 29, and 84.64.</p>
</div>
